Re: Learning to read japanese books?
by clay » Mon 04.06.2009 11:34 am After you have learned basic grammar and have a beginner's vocabulary, you may want to start with some manga (especially short stories or 4 koma comics). There's usually a lot of slang, but with the visual clues, it can be a good way for even the beginner to learn spoken Japanese while reading!
