by astaroth » Mon 04.06.2009 12:25 pm kentaku_sama wrote:Why would you need a dictionary? Can't you just know all the words?Eventually. I guess. But I'm a physicist and eventually for us means after an infinite amount of time.So I guess one never knows all the words. After living in US for 6+ more years I can read novels, newspaper, and watch a movie without help of a dictionary (or subtitles), though I still encounter a word I don't know from time to time but I can usually infer the meaning from the context.I think two years to be able to read novels and newspapers in a language you just started studying is a bit on the short side.Obviously that shouldn't discourage you from your studies, but just simply put that in a perspective.clay wrote:manga (especially short stories or 4 koma comics).Sorry, clay. What's 4koma?
